60044598.m_KeyValue: ""Deeply committed to the honor of his people, an elder established this tradition to inspire young Bloodborn on their mission to the moon. Those awarded the Medal of Honor receive the elder's highest blessings and unwavering support.""

111117374.m_KeyValue: "Was any of it real? Or just dreams dressed up in memory?"

111117377.m_KeyValue: "(The collar's too tight… This mantle feels like it's choking me)"

111117380.m_KeyValue: "I'm starving. This really is the waking world."

111117382.m_KeyValue: "_$$Sleeping here with me for a century_$$—weren't those your own words?"

111117383.m_KeyValue: ""Until then, wait for me... and want for me, my beloved Vassal.""

111117384.m_KeyValue: "I will make you keep that promise."

163451765.m_KeyValue: "Complete the current chapter to unlock the next one."

188548467.m_KeyValue: ""Desert dwellers came to this place twice—once a century ago in pursuit of new lands, and a hundred years later in chains. The rare blue crystal mines turned the desert into a treasure trove for nobles, but they also became the final resting place for countless enslaved desert inhabitants.""

188548468.m_KeyValue: ""The frozen blue lake stands high between the Astolfo and Montebello families. Beneath its untouched surface, an ancient verse echoes: A lake upon the heights, illuminated by the Other Side, sings of a child divine.""

188548469.m_KeyValue: ""Adamm Astolfo, the sage who once led the desert people in their wandering, established the first desert tribe along this river. Though the tribe has long since vanished, the river bears the sage's name as its lasting legacy.""

188548470.m_KeyValue: ""Stone pillars stand solemnly in the desert sands, engraved with records of the Astolfo family's southward migration along the oases. Yet their ancestral dwellings have crumbled to ruin, and the elders who have passed sealed away this history, burying unspeakable secrets of the past.""

188548472.m_KeyValue: ""Once believed to bring prosperity to the desert with the fall of a meteorite, this deep western crater is now encrusted with cobalt-blue crystals, marking the inescapable doom of the Astolfo clan.""

188548473.m_KeyValue: ""Children of the desert often sing this rhyme: Water flows where sands run dry, trees shall bloom and touch the sky. A bard roams from town to east, to seek a land of peace at least. Yet long ago, this verdant land, belonged to another's hand.""

188548474.m_KeyValue: ""This narrow mountain path, northeast of Sandspire Keep, is the only route to the outside world. After the Campaign began, it became a burial ground for fallen Vassals. Though frost has replaced the desert sands, the weapon marks carved into the surrounding cliffs remain as eternal scars.""

188548479.m_KeyValue: ""_$$We extolled our ancestors for their protection, we extolled the Divine for our victories. Now, with nowhere else to turn, we must extol once more—for the future of our people._$$""

188548480.m_KeyValue: ""After countless migrations, the desert dwellers finally built high walls atop the central dunes. Yet the peace they longed for crumbled under relentless conflict, leaving only restless spirits to wander the sands.""

312576208.m_KeyValue: ""Friedrich remained motionless with his arms across his chest. He gazed at his companion and challenged, 'Are you giving me an order, or a suggestion?'""

312576209.m_KeyValue: ""'We'll split into two search parties,' Gilrain declared, taking charge to prevent idling. 'I'll head east along the shore while you two go west.'""

326104736.m_KeyValue: ""The trio crested the hill, venturing into a birch forest. A spectral mist coiled between the trees, swirling around the long-awaited visitors like curious, ghostly tendrils.""

326104737.m_KeyValue: ""Aiona, seemingly accustomed to their antics, observed, 'The Eye of God mentioned on the linen must be this place. Now, where could this key lead us?'""

348904983.m_KeyValue: ""'Back then, King Johan the Red claimed it was the divine guidance of shooting stars that led his army eastward, rendering him invincible...' Well, it seems we overestimated Empousa's ability to lighten the mood.""

348904984.m_KeyValue: ""Jestel, of course, couldn't accept this view. 'How can two people finding true love be a disaster?' she protested.""

348904986.m_KeyValue: "'Aren't you joining us in the search for the Moonblessed?' Noah suddenly realized this would also mark a moment of separation."

455524922.m_KeyValue: "Continue exploring other areas for more rewards."

463329125.m_KeyValue: ""The arcane rites of the ancients. Originally intended for self-enhancement, they were soon apprehended by the Bloodborn. After many massacres, the ultimate secret behind the ritual would be discovered: By offering souls similar in essence to the ritual's subject, the purest form of ancestral power could be harnessed.""

1531973247.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Dusk Castle
<style=""InfoText"">The night deepens as the moon cries resoundingly. As the castle stands alone, it lies forever within the moon's embrace.
• From here you may enter rooms with varying functions.
• Some rooms have been sealed for ages and need to be unlocked with a key, which can be obtained by advancing Threads of Fate.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Observatory
<style=""InfoText"">The arrangement and movements of the stars are no mere coincidence; they signify cycles of cause and effect on the continent.
• Utilize Prophecy Inscriptions to unlock constellations and observe their Stars for bonuses.
• Advance Threads of Fate to uncover clues about Prophecy Inscriptions and explore the map to locate them.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Hall of Honor
<style=""InfoText"">Your honor transforms into blessings for the future.
• Complete Achievements to earn Medals of Prestige. Accumulate these medals to upgrade your Hall of Honor Level.
• Upgrading the Hall unlocks honorary statues and rewards, some of which provide permanent bonuses.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Ritual Chamber
<style=""InfoText"">This ancient soul-alchemy ritual sacrifices souls of similar quality to extract potent Ancestral Power from them.
• The Ritual Chamber can enhance Vassals' attributes universally.
• All Ritual level caps are limited by Bloodline Transfusion Levels.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Bloodline Transfusion
<style=""InfoText"">The secret technique of the Bloodborn grants all living souls, no matter how young, powerful abilities by transfusing their blood with that of the ancients.
• The 5 highest-level Vassals will automatically join the transfusion.
• The Transfusion level will be determined by the lowest-level Vassal among the chosen five.
• Vassals that are newly-added to the Transfusion Bar will be automatically upgraded to the Transfusion level. Vassals in the Transfusion Bar cannot be upgraded independently.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Moonlight Tribute
<style=""InfoText"">Moonlight Tribute is an essential ritual that the Bathory family must observe.
• For every 5 stages cleared in Normal Mode or Hard Mode in Threads of Fate, Moonlight Faith increases by 1 level. As Moonlight Faith increases, so do Tribute yields.
• You can perform a limited number of Extra Sermons each day. Through Extra Sermon, you will immediately gain basic resources and random item rewards equal to 2 hours of ritual time.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Wilderness Expedition
<style=""InfoText"">Most Bloodborn follow the tenet of Secrecy, but should they truly wish to restore their past glory, Lords must dispatch Vassals to explore the continent for lost treasures.
• Different expeditions require Vassals of different factions and rarities.
• Higher-star expeditions require longer completion times and higher-rarity Vassals.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Starlit Memoir
<style=""InfoText"">On moonlit nights, Vassals venture outside the castle walls and play in the surrounding areas. It is here where little stories often unfold.
• Each story requires Candles to access. Candles represent the number of stories available this week.
• Earn a reward for completing each Memoir.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Council Chamber
<style=""InfoText"">The ancient castle is a place of intrigue, where Lords gather with their confidants to discuss topics such as internal affairs, diplomatic plans, or personal matters.
• Every day, Lords will randomly receive topics of discussion. Lords can choose which topics to discuss based on their own preferences.
• Each Vassal that participates in the meeting gains Affinity.""

1531973248.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Building Unlocked
<style=""InfoText"">The Rare Specimen Gallery clearly embodies one single ambition: Establishing itself as a universal symbol through total control.
• Advance Threads of Fate to uncover clues about Keys and explore the map to find the doors they unlock.
• Use Keys to access new rooms and unveil the past.""

1531973249.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Building Unlocked
<style=""InfoText"">During the era of the Crimson Inquisition, the Bathory family hid Ancestries with special Blood Powers inside their cellar, preserving them for a future rebirth.
• Advance Threads of Fate to uncover clues about Keys and explore the map to find the doors they unlock.
• Use Keys to access new rooms and unveil the past.""

1531973250.m_KeyValue:
""Duke it out with other Lords in the BO3 matches.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Season
<style=""InfoText"">• A season consists of both an Engagement and Armistice period. The Engagement period lasts for 13 days, while the Armistice lasts for 1 day.
• If you initiate an attack and win, you will switch rankings with your opponent. If you are attacked and fail to defend, you will also switch rankings with your opponent.
• At the end of each season, the Etched Keystone (Crucible Points) will be reset.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Challenge</style>
<style=""InfoText"">• Select an opponent you want to challenge from the Opponent List.
• You will only be matched against higher-ranking players.
• You have 2 free challenge attempts per day.
• Once your free attempts are used up, you may use Crucible Passes to engage in more battles.
• A challenge consists of a Preparation Phase and a Battle Phase.
• If you quit or time out during the Preparation Phase, the challenge will end and no attempts will be consumed.
• If you time out during the Battle Phase, it will be considered a failure (each of the 3 battles is independently timed).

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Defense Team
<style=""InfoText"">Tap _$$Edit Team_$$ to deploy your lineup. When challenged by other Lords, your Defense Team will defend your glory. You must build 3 teams, ensuring that each team contains 5 Vassals.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Offense Team
<style=""InfoText"">You may build your Offense Team after selecting an opponent and entering battle.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Winning Conditions
<style=""InfoText"">The team that eliminates the other team first wins. Should the two teams be eliminated at the same time, the attacker wins. If you time out during the Battle Phase, it will be considered a failure (each of the 3 battles is independently timed).

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Rewards
<style=""InfoText"">• Winning the battle earns you rewards.
• After a season ends, season ranking rewards will be issued via Mail.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Hourly Rewards
<style=""InfoText""> • Hourly idle rewards vary based on your rank; the higher the rank, the greater the rewards.
• Idle rewards also include Points, so achieving a higher rank can help you earn more Points, allowing you to secure a top spot on the Point Rank!

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Quick Battle
<style=""InfoText""> • When Quick Battle is enabled, battle results will be displayed directly.
• Use the Replay function to watch the battle again (may not be 100% accurate).""

1531973253.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Truth's Odyssey
<style=""InfoText"">• Set off on a journey to solve various contingencies and discover the wonders of enlightenment.
• All progress in this mode will reset daily at a specified time.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Embark
<style=""InfoText"">• Choose your preferred difficulty and Chamber.
• Chambers will be gradually unlocked by clearing [Threads of Fate].
• Each Chamber contains 3 difficulties. A new difficulty unlocks upon a successful challenge of the previous one.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※Chambers
<style=""InfoText"">• Each difficulty consists of multiple stages.
• For each stage, you can choose random or fixed Elements.
• These include Wind Elements, Earth Elements, Aether Elements, Water Elements, etc.
• After clearing all stages in one difficulty, you may claim rewards and proceed to the next.
• Clearance Rewards may only be obtained once per day.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Wind Elements
<style=""InfoText"">• Divided into three tiers: Wind Element I, Wind Element II, and Fire Element.
• Upon completing, you will gain Catalyst rewards.
• The higher the difficulty, the higher the chance of obtaining High-Grade Catalysts.
• Vassals will not recover HP after each challenge.
• Enemy units also cannot recover HP should the stage remain incomplete.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Catalysts
<style=""InfoText"">• Provide special effects for Vassals participating in battle.
• However, Catalysts only apply to eligible targets.
• Catalysts are divided into four Grades: N, R, SR, and SSR. The strength of the effect increases with the Grade.
• The strength of Catalysts also increases with their Aspect Level.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Catalyst Aspects
<style=""InfoText"">• The Aspect Level will increase based on the number of Catalysts of the same Aspect type held.
• Catalysts are divided into 4 Aspects: Triangle, Diamond, Circle, and Square. Each Catalyst belongs to one of these Aspects.
• Catalyst Aspect Levels:
• LV1: Base state
• LV2: Hold 3 of the same Aspect type
• LV3: Hold 4 of the same Aspect type
• LV4: Hold 6 of the same Aspect type
• LV5: Hold 8 of the same Aspect type

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Aether Elements
<style=""InfoText"">• Triggers various Wonders, each providing different effects based on your selection.
• Effects will impact the status of Vassals and their Catalysts.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Water Elements
<style=""InfoText"">• You can choose to restore Vassal HP or revive Vassals.
• You must choose between restoration or revival.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※Stop
<style=""InfoText"">• You may end the Odyssey manually, or end through completion after clearing the final area.
• After the Odyssey ends, all progress will be reset.

2694772657.m_KeyValue:
""Leveling up is the most effective way to increase Vassals' base attributes, but it is subject to their level cap.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Level Up
<style=""InfoText"">Vassals start at LV. 1 and can be leveled up using certain materials. Besides this, Vassals can also be leveled up through the Bloodline Transfusion.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Level Limit
<style=""InfoText"">Vassal level-ups are subject to their own level cap and the following rules:
• Own 5 LV. 40 Vassals to increase level cap to 60.
• Own 5 LV. 60 Vassals to increase level cap to 80.
• Own 5 LV. 80 Vassals to increase level cap to 100.
• Own 5 LV. 100 Vassals to increase level cap to 120.
• Own 5 LV. 120 Vassals to increase level cap to 140.
• Own 5 LV. 140 Vassals to increase level cap to 160.
• Own 5 LV. 160 Vassals to increase level cap to 180.
• Own 5 LV. 180 Vassals to increase level cap to 200.
• Own 5 LV. 200 Vassals to remove level cap.""

2694772658.m_KeyValue:
""Equipment is an advanced method of enhancing Vassal abilities. The higher its level and quality, the more noticeable the effects will be.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Equipment Pieces
<style=""InfoText"">There are 4 pieces that can be equipped: Head, Body, Amulet, and Ring. Each slot can only equip the corresponding piece.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Equipment Types
<style=""InfoText"">There are 3 types of equipment: Light, Medium, and Heavy. Vassals can only equip pieces from their default type.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Faction Bonus
<style=""InfoText"">Certain equipment enjoys faction bonuses, meaning it can have bonus stats activated (usually +25%) if worn by a Vassal of the corresponding faction.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Enhancement
<style=""InfoText"">High-quality equipment can be enhanced. The higher its enhance level, the stronger its attributes become.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Soul Echo
<style=""InfoText"">Soul Echo can be performed with Soulstrike for equipment that meets the following requirements:
• Tier 9 equipment with faction bonuses
• Equipped by Vassals of the right faction
• Enhanced to the max level
After activation, the equipment is bound to the Vassal and gains the following effects:
• Cannot be unequipped
• Provides more powerful attributes
• Gains up to 3 Blessings. Blessings may offer a significant boost to Vassals
• Can be Reforged or Refined later to change Blessing effects.""

2694772661.m_KeyValue:
""In the darkest recesses of the world, countless threads of fate have interwoven tightly. Hence, what is about to unfold is not the future, but an event that has already transpired.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Modes
<style=""InfoText"">Chose from Normal mode and Hard mode. Note that Hard mode unlocks after progressing in Normal mode. Also, enemies in Hard mode are more formidable, so proceed with caution!

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ EX Stage
<style=""InfoText"">EX Stages will appear once certain progress in a chapter has been made. Enemies in EX Stages are all extremely powerful, and units on both sides will be set to a certain LV.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Fated Ties
<style=""InfoText"">Could the items encountered along your journey have once been treasures cherished by a lost soul? Occasionally, the threads of fate intertwine briefly, only to quickly unravel once more.
• Clues may be revealed while progressing through certain chapters. Use these Clues to seek out hidden locations on the world map and discover lost items.
• Some locations contain Lost Memories belonging to various individuals. By completing sets of Lost Memories, certain rewards will become available. View more details in [Fated Ties] — [Lost Memories].""

2694772662.m_KeyValue:
""Duke it out with other Lords for power and glory. If victorious, you will receive Marks of Bravery, which may be exchanged for rewards in the [Shop - Blood Shop].

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Fair Play
<style=""InfoText"">• All teams will be set to LV. 200.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Season
<style=""InfoText"">• A season consists of both an Engagement and Armistice period. The Engagement period lasts for 13 days, while the Armistice lasts for 1 day.
• Winning a battle grants you Points while losing one costs you Points. Your ranking is decided by your total Points.
• At the end of a season, your Points will be reset to around 1,000.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Challenge</style>
<style=""InfoText"">• Select an opponent you want to challenge from the Opponent List.
• You have 3 free challenges per day.
• When free attempts are used up, you may use Arena Pass to engage in more challenges. There is a daily purchase limit for Arena Pass.
• A challenge consists of a Preparation Phase and a Battle Phase.
• If you quit or time out during the Preparation Phase, the challenge will be canceled and no challenge attempts will be consumed.
• If you quit or time out during the Battle Phase, your challenge will be considered a failure, which will result in the consumption of your challenge attempt, thus Points will be settled accordingly.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Defense Team
<style=""InfoText"">Tap Edit Team to arrange your lineup. When challenged by other Lords, your Defense Team will take on the challenge and defend your glory.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Offense Team
<style=""InfoText"">You can edit your Offense Team after you select an opponent and enter the battle.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Winning Conditions
<style=""InfoText"">The team that defeats the other team first wins. If the two teams tie for victory, they both win. If the attacker quits or times out in the Battle Phase, their challenge will be considered a failure.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Rewards
<style=""InfoText"">• Achieving victory in the battle earns you Victory Rewards.
• Daily rank rewards will be issued via Mail every day.
• After a season ends, season rank rewards will be issued via Mail.""

2694772663.m_KeyValue:
""Send your loyal Vassals on hired missions! Mercenary Hunting Ground offers attractive Skill Upgrade materials.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Mercenary Hunting Ground
<style=""InfoText"">Earn rewards based on kills, up to 3 hunts per day. Please manage your hunts wisely!

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Quick Clear
<style=""InfoText"">Achieve a score in any hunt to unlock Quick Clear for that day (consumes hunt attempts). Rewards will be based on your best score of the day.""

2694772664.m_KeyValue:
""Transfuse with family blood, and inherit will of the strong. Bloodline Transfusion can help level up your Vassals and even raise their level cap. 

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Transfusion Vassals
<style=""InfoText"">The 5 highest-level Vassals will automatically join the transfusion.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Transfusion Level 
<style=""InfoText"">Transfusion level will be limited to the lowest level of the 5 participating Vassals. 

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Transfusion Slot 
<style=""InfoText"">Newly-added Vassal will be upgraded to the set Transfusion level automatically. However, Vassals in Transfusion cannot be upgraded independently. 
• In some cases, Transfusion level can be higher than a Vassal's max level.""

2694772665.m_KeyValue:
""Moonlight Tribute is essential for the Bathory family, and it will be a key source of basic enhancement materials.
<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Moonlight Faith
<style=""InfoText"">Every 5 clears in Threads of Fate, either in Normal mode or Hard mode, increases Moonlight Faith by 1 level. Moonlight Faith increases Tribute gains.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Extra Sermon
<style=""InfoText"">You may perform Sermon a limited number of times per day, immediately gaining basic resources and random item rewards equal to 2 hours of ritual time each time.""

2694772666.m_KeyValue:
""This is where your loyal Vassals gather. To view specific rules about Vassal development, go to the development tab in Vassal details and tap the [!] icon in the top left corner.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Blood Power
<style=""InfoText"">Blood Power represents the overall combat ability of a Vassal. Developing Vassals can enhance their Blood Power rating, and you can develop Vassals through various means, including but not limited to: leveling up, skill enhancement, equipment development, Future Artifacts, Ritual Chamber, Affinity, etc.""

2694772667.m_KeyValue:
""Legend holds that each blade in the tomb has befallen a Blood Beast. As time passes, however, the blood shed transforms into dark spirits that linger below.
Take on these powerful spirits in the Tomb of the Fallen to obtain Equipment! 

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Tomb of the Fallen
<style=""InfoText"">There are 4 major stages that unlock as you progress through Threads of Fate. 

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Exorcise Spirit
<style=""InfoText"">Use Exorcise attempts to take on spirits and earn rewards.
Exorcise attempts are shared between all stages and reset daily. 

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Spirit Fragments
<style=""InfoText""> Spirit Fragments represent the total DMG dealt to a spirit.
The higher the accumulated DMG dealt to a spirit, the more Fragments you'll receive, and thus the better the rewards.
As your Spirit Fragment count increases, spirits will grow stronger.
Spirit Fragments reset daily for each stage. Daily Spirit Fragment records are only recorded when fighting manually. 

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Quick Battle
<style=""InfoText"">After manually fighting a spirit, you may use Quick Battle, which is based on the best attempt that day. 

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Trial Exorcism
<style=""InfoText"">You may practice on all unlocked stages.
Trial Exorcism does not consume daily attempts, but it does not count towards Spirit Fragments, nor does it provide rewards.""

2694772668.m_KeyValue:
""Towers and Abysses appear as opposing forces. Yet, as you climb upwards here, you eventually… plummet further into the depths. Advance in Infinite Abyss to earn Moon Tear and Faction Vassal Shards!

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Infinite Abyss
<style=""InfoText"">Venture into the abyss to take down enemies. The farther you progress, the stronger the enemies you encounter. Infinite Abyss consists of the Tower of Purification and 4 Faction Abysses.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Tower of Purification
<style=""InfoText"">Accessible throughout the day, you may enter with all your Vassals and there are no faction restrictions.

<style=""InfoTitle"">※ Faction Abysses
<style=""InfoText"">These consist of Tower of Decay, Tower of Original Sin, Tower of Desire, and Tower of Deception. Each corresponds to a faction, and is open for a limited time. Only faction Vassals can enter!""

3827538599.m_KeyValue: ""Legend has it that this Celestial God was known in the celestial realm for its compassion, having rescued condemned and exiled Celestial Gods from the Nether Abyss many times with its powerful arms. Those inspired by this Celestial God will view hardships as a path of temperament, and atonement as necessary in the journey of self-cultivation.""

4230823126.m_KeyValue: ""Legend has it that this Celestial God has a pair of hard horns. Due to their strong competitive nature, they once broke the leg of the Celestial God Sagittarius in a divine battle, which earned them a severe punishment from the celestial realm as well as the complete loss of their memory. Since then, they have traversed the Sea of Stars guided merely by instinct. Those who inherit its legacy will possess an unyielding will, advancing without the need to question whether the path beneath their feet is correct, for progress itself is the meaning.""

4277877293.m_KeyValue: ""Legend has it that this Celestial God has extraordinary wisdom, often coming up with ingenious solutions to conflicts among Celestial Gods. Their wisdom lay not in foreseeing the future, but in understanding the present and exploring the correct position of each step taken. Those blessed by this Celestial God will receive its gift of wisdom, rendering them able to hastily formulate meticulous strategies to resolve crises.""

4287641917.m_KeyValue: ""'Hehe.' Empousa's lips curled into a self-satisfied smirk. Despite teasing the amnesiac protagonist, she felt not an ounce of remorse.""

4287641919.m_KeyValue: "That's truly nothing more than a legend."

4287641920.m_KeyValue: ""'However, the book mentions an alternative account.' Empousa, sensing the oppressive atmosphere, attempted to salvage the situation.""
